SecureDispatch Changelog

Version 1.0.0 (2024-02-15)
- Initial release of SecureDispatch
- Implemented basic functionality to send one-time passwords (OTPs) via email
- Included support for Gmail SMTP service
- Added error handling for email sending failures

Version 1.1.0 (2024-03-01)
- Added support for custom SMTP servers
- Enhanced OTP generation algorithm for improved randomness
- Improved error logging for easier troubleshooting
- Fixed minor bugs and improved code readability

Version 1.2.0 (2024-03-15)
- Introduced premium version with additional features
- Added enhanced security measures for premium users
- Included priority support for premium users
- Implemented advanced customization options for premium users
- Provided exclusive access to future updates and features for premium users
- Enhanced documentation and added licensing information

Version 1.2.1 (2024-03-20)
- Fixed compatibility issues with certain email providers
- Improved email delivery reliability
- Addressed reported security vulnerabilities
- Updated dependencies to ensure compatibility with the latest versions

Version 1.3.0 (2024-04-05)
- Added multi-language support for email templates
- Introduced user-friendly configuration options
- Improved performance and scalability
- Enhanced logging for better monitoring and analytics
- Optimized code for faster execution

Version 1.3.1 (2024-04-10)
- Fixed regression issue with OTP generation
- Improved handling of edge cases in email sending process
- Addressed feedback from users and implemented minor enhancements

